title: I don't want to use birdeye-api in plugin-solana!
body:
I'm having the same problem as I just want to implement creating and selling tokens on pumpfun and don't want to get portfolio information through Birdeye API and the free version of the package doesn't have access to the interface /v1/wallet/token_list, so is there any way to bypass him?

body:
**Describe the bug**
I have encountered this issue both locally on Windows and in WSL2.
Have any developers from mainland China encountered this problem? I can access the AI server normally using apipost. But Eliza just can't do it.
I tried openai, grok, and gemini, but none of them worked.
I tried the global proxy mode, but it didn't work.
